    <body>
      <section eId="sec_580_314">
        <num>580-314</num>
        <heading>Limited immunity of petitioner</heading>
        <subsection eId="sec_580_314__subsec_a">
          <num>(a)</num>
          <content>
            <p>Participation by a\npetitioner in a proceeding under this article before a responding\ntribunal, whether in person, by private attorney or through services\nprovided by the support enforcement agency, does not confer personal\njurisdiction over the petitioner in another proceeding.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_580_314__subsec_b">
          <num>(b)</num>
          <content>
            <p>A petitioner is not amenable to service of civil process while\nphysically present in this state to participate in a proceeding under\nthis article.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_580_314__subsec_c">
          <num>(c)</num>
          <content>
            <p>The immunity granted by this section does not extend to civil\nlitigation based on acts unrelated to a proceeding under this article\ncommitted by a party while physically present in this state to\nparticipate in the proceeding.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
      </section>
